and Presentation API for Unix)](/wiki/VDPAU \"VDPAU\")\n* [X-Video Bitstream Acceleration (XvBA)](/wiki/X-Video_Bitstream_Acceleration \"X-Video Bitstream Acceleration\"), the X11 equivalent of DXVA for MPEG-2, H.264, and VC-1\n* [X-Video Motion Compensation](/wiki/X-Video_Motion_Compensation \"X-Video Motion Compensation\") – the X11 equivalent for MPEG-2 video codec only\n\n### Applications\n\n[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Graphics_processing_unit&action=edit&section=22 \"Edit section: Applications\")]\n\n* [GPU cluster](/wiki/GPU_cluster \"GPU cluster\")\n* [Mathematica](/wiki/Mathematica \"Mathematica\") – includes built-in support for CUDA and OpenCL GPU execution\n* [Molecular modeling on GPU](/wiki/Molecular_modeling_on_GPU \"Molecular modeling on GPU\")\n* [Deeplearning4j](/wiki/Deeplearning4j \"Deeplearning4j\") – open-source, distributed deep learning for Java\n\nReferences\n----------\n\n[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Graphics_processing_unit&action=edit&section=23 \"Edit section: References\")]\n\n1. ^ [***a***](#cite_ref-Peddie_1-0) [***b***](#cite_ref-Peddie_1-1) [***c***](#cite_ref-Peddie_1-2) [***d***](#cite_ref-Peddie_1-3) Jon Peddie (2022). *The History of the GPU - Steps to Invention* (1st ed.). Springer. p. 424. [ISBN](/wiki/ISBN_(identifier) \"ISBN (identifier)\") [978-3031109676](/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-3031109676 \"Special:BookSources/978-3031109676\").\n2. **[^](#cite_ref-2)** Hague, James (September 10, 2013). [\"Why Do Dedicated Game Consoles Exist?\"](https://web.archive.org/web/20150504042057/https://prog21.dadgum.com/181.html). *Programming in the 21st Century*. Archived from [the original](https://prog21.dadgum.com/181.html) on May 4, 2015. Retrieved November 11, 2015.\n3. **[^](#cite_ref-3)** [\"mame/8080bw.c at master 路 mamedev/mame 路 GitHub\"](https://github.com/mamedev/mame/tree/master/src/mame/drivers/8080bw.c). *GitHub*.`{{cite web}}`: CS1 maint: deprecated archival service ([link](/wiki/Category:CS1_maint:_deprecated_archival_serv